tweet: There is still much to do. Together, let’s recommit ourselves to working toward a cure to finally #ENDALZ .
Our work continues this Congress, which is why I’m cosponsoring the Younger Onset Alzheimer's Act, which expands services available to those under age 60 who have been diagnosed with Alzheimer’s.
Last Congress, I proudly cosponsored the BOLD Infrastructure for  Alzheimer’s Act – now law – to strengthen public health infrastructure  for Alzheimer’s patients across our country.

June is Alzheimer’s Awareness Month. An estimated 5.8 million Americans are currently fighting this devastating illness, and they need our support. Today, my staff and I are wearing purple to support Alzheimer’s patients and those who care for them. pic.twitter.com/dDJFnmby7V

Today, I spoke from the House Floor against a Democrat-led effort to turn back the progress we’ve made, both for Alaska and for American energy independence.

Many of my Democrat colleagues have never even stepped foot in our great state and yet have no problem trying to make decisions for Alaska. Opening up ANWR is a settled issue, and for a long time, ANWR exploration was also a bipartisan priority.

The State supports it. Alaskans support it. The Arctic Iñupiat who live there support it. And yet today, House Democrats are once again trying to shut down oil exploration in ANWR -- telling Alaskans how they should be using their land. pic.twitter.com/1l7VSezToT
